race.comment: MINI ANGEL (1) is fresh from a spell of 12 weeks and has switched from the premier Victorian stable. Won a Moe Maiden easily thee back and that stacks right up. She's placed fresh and has a low gate and handy 2kg claim. MISS WATERLINE (9) resumes and has won fresh. She's trialled well and would be very competitive at best. Draws inside and will get every chance. SUPERSONIC MAN (2) is ex-HK and should be a quick improver in the Campton yard. Has a tough draw to overcome but can make his presence felt. ALL TOO FOXY (10) found it too tough in town at the latest but this is much easier and comes straight back into serious contention.
